description.narrative: Girls and boys and their mothers living in humanitarian conditions have access to life saving health interventions from pregnancy to adolescence.,which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable use of high-impact maternal, newborn, child health and nutrition specific and sensitive interventions.

description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF supported emergency response for cholera, diphtheria and measles; catering for 40 % of suspected cholera cases in 18 governorates and 132 districts. In total, 1.9 people were provided oral cholera vaccine in seven high-risk districts and 3 million children protected against diphtheria through response campaign. | Status:Met | As-of Date:15/01/2020
